🎥 NEW VIDEO NOW LIVE 

We’ve been a bit MIA on the old Instagram during the bike trip, whilst we’ve been posting weekly on YouTube we’ve not had much time (or energy) to be updating you here too. 

We just uploaded video 4 of the bike trip. We’d decided to part ways and we were learning the hard way that we had to listen to our bodies and get the rest and fuel we needed in order to be able to continue this adventure. 

We were also learning that ‘fuel’ looks different for everyone. 

For me, I needed rest and lots of honey and lemon as I’d developed a cold (probs from sleeping in a tent during one too many thunderstorms) 
For Josh, that was getting a sense of achievement through hitting that 500 mile point (and beer, and coffee - as illustrated in these images).

Anyway, if you want to catch up with the latest antics you can use the link in our bio or searching ‘Wandering Home’ on YouTube. 

✌🏼

#bikepacking #travel #explore #adventure #cycletouring #cyclelife

Hey strangers 👋🏼

It’s been a while, we took an unexpected break over Christmas to rest our tired bodies (and minds). Turns out cycling 800+ miles can really take it out of you 😅

Just popping our faces on here to say hello, thanks to those who have messaged to check in. It means a lot. 

The full series of our cycling trip is all up on YouTube so our next video will be us learning what 5 months parked up in the sun can do to an old campervan like Bluey. 
What do we reckon? Did she do us proud? 

#vanlife #travel #vanlifetravel

Chilly January days making us even more grateful for the long, warm days that fill Summer. 

Oh to be living outside, wearing shorts and worrying about parking in the shade.

#MadeForOutside #ColumbiaEU #ad

I don’t think I’ll ever be able to recreate how this moment felt but this feels pretty close. 

We walked into our hotel room after a long, difficult few days cycling and were greeted with sunset peeping through the curtains. When we drew them back there it was, thousands of birds swirling around the city centre. Just what we needed to see and just the right time. 

🕊️

#naturalphenomenon #naturephotography #drone #dronephotography #murmuration #wildlife #lifequotes

putting #MadeForOutside to the test. 

We’ve gotten to know our Columbia gear quite well over the past few years working with them. We’ve learnt about how much time and energy they invest into technologies that they’ve pioneered. Plus, with 80 years of product, they’ve got some serious heritage and heart behind them too. 

💪🏼 Did you know it was run by Gert Boyle, a serious power-house of a woman for 30+ years? If you don’t know about her, it’s time you learnt!

Packing for the bike trip was a test in minimal packing but our must-pack @columbia_eu items included…

• Josh’s Technical Tee (the bright orange one worn pretty much daily) has Omni-Freeze and Omni-Wick technology that actually reacts with your sweat to cool you down 🤯 #mindblown 
• Charlie’s Omni-Heat Infinity jacket, with snazzy gold lining that reflects your body heat kept me cosy on cool November nights but also doubled up as a decent camping pillow at night too #multipurpose
• Joshs Waterproof jacket gave the OutDry Extreme tech the ultimate test by cycling down the west coast of France in November in a torrential downpour. It also packs away super small, ideal when you’re limited to a few pannier bags. 
• Final item I couldn’t not mention, are you even camping if you don’t bring a fleece? Absolutely essential. 

#ad

This moment deserves a permanent spot on here.

Back to YouTube this Sunday for what happened when we got to Bluey! But for now, let’s just celebrate our biggest achievement of cycling 800+ miles to get to her 🫶🏼✨

We've been a little quiet on here lately as we needed to take a step away for a while and reflect, so thank you for your patience and to all of you who reached out to check in. 🙏 

Growing this small creative idea into the space we have has been an incredible experience. It was born in 2020 lockdown as a way to share with family and friends the bus we were converting but it soon grew beyond our expectations. 

This space allowed us to connect during a time of disconnection. 
It brought us incredibly supportive friendships both online and in real life that we will always cherish (you know who you are).
It allowed us to pursue dreams of travel, living alternatively and prioritising lifestyle. 
It was an outlet for our creativity in ways we didn't even know. 
It helped us launch a business and work with a brand who we respect and admire (we still pinch oursevles about that second part).
It is something we are so proud of creating and building together. 

However, we have decided it is time to close this chapter. Whilst we had so many ideas and plans for Wandering Home, we recognise that our priorities have shifted in the last 6 months and we are ready to explore that privately for now.

I read a great quote recently that said:
I think things are not meant to last so that for the short time they are here, we are able to appreciate them and love them so much more fully than if they lasted forever. 

We hope you understand this decision and honestly can't thank you enough for the opportunities and memories we've created through sharing on here. 
BIG BIG BIG Love, x

PS. Charlie here, to those of you who I have connected with on here that would like to stay in touch, I do have a personal account too and would love to hear from you, you're very special people to me 💕  @charlie_osman
